      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SECRET STORY (4) goes very well this trip starting 23 times for 15 wins and seven minors. In the money last time at Capalaba (19.79) in a Free For All, finishing a 2.5 lengths third. Expected to go close. COUSIN HENRY (8) was strongly supported last start when a short priced favourite and duly saluted winning by a neck at this track in a handy 18.98. Outside box to overcome but goes well at this distance. Recorded one of the quickest times on the card in scoring last start. In sparkling form and looks the one to beat again. ZIPPING SCHRUB (5) boasts a strong record this journey with six wins and three minors from 10 tries. Missed the frame latest (19.86) when fourth over 366m at Capalaba in a Grade 5. Looks one of the chances. RANNOCH (2) found the frame for the second consecutive time when narrowly beaten into second last time out (18.97) over 350m at this track.",
